The 34 Artillery Brigade of the Nigerian Army in Obinze, near Owerri, the Imo State capital, has commenced the destruction of unserviceable ammunition and explosives. A statement on Friday by the Acting Assistant Director of Army Public Relations, Lt. Babatunde Zubairu, made the announcement. The spokesman said the exercise would be conducted by the 82 Base Ammunition Depot, Enugu from May 14 to May 21. Zubairu added that the demolition would take place between 7am and 5pm daily throughout the period. The residents of Obinze and surrounding communities were advised to stay away from the range area for now. “This is not a cause for alarm as the Nigerian Army remains committed to the safety of Nigerians,” the statement read.